Shipmates is evolving into an AI‑powered, course‑centric study app that turns students’ notes into shared quizzes and flashcards they can use with their classmates.

Shipmates direction (high‑level)
Shipmates helps college students learn faster by:

Letting them upload or paste class notes for each course.

Using generative AI to automatically create high‑quality flashcards and quiz questions from those notes.

Letting course‑mates share, edit, and study from these decks together inside small groups, with light social features (chat, sessions, basic stats).

In one line:

Shipmates is an AI‑powered study platform that converts your course notes into collaborative flashcards and quizzes you can study with your classmates.

Key user flows in this direction
Students join or create course spaces and small study groups.

For a given course, a student can paste notes or upload text/PDF excerpts.

Shipmates’ AI engine generates:

Flashcards (question/answer style, definitions, concepts).

Quiz questions (multiple choice/short answer) aligned to that course.

Students can review, edit, and approve AI‑generated cards, then:

Add them to shared course decks.

Use built‑in quiz/flashcard modes to study.

See which decks their friends or group are using.

Social stays focused and light: group chats, sharing decks into groups, and maybe simple progress indicators (e.g., “You and 3 friends studied this deck this week”).

How this ties to your requirements
Generative AI is core, not a side feature: it’s what creates the study material from notes.

You still demonstrate full software engineering: requirements, system design (frontend, backend, DB, AI service), implementation, testing, and evaluation of AI output quality.

On a resume, you can frame it as building an end‑to‑end AI study companion around real college courses and collaboration.